race.description: Celebrating The Life Of Craig Wake Handicap
race.comment: AMARLIE MISS (6) has been crying out for more ground in her last couple of starts, and she will relish getting out to a mile at this level. The key here will be having William Pike back in the saddle, and she is the one to beat. POLYVANOVA (1) ran a much better race in her second start from the local Paul Hunter stable when finishing runner-up here 9 days ago. She benefits once again from a 4kg claim and should hold her form now. LORDGIVEMESTRENGTH (10) drops back from a middle distance, and she did win her only start here over a mile. Stick with her for all top 4 combos. KAMIKAZE FIGHTER (7) has raced his way back into form, finishing in the money third up from a spell here a month ago. Each way value in this. SIR BEAR A LOT (5) peaked on his run late when resuming from a spell here 9 days ago over 1240m. He has not missed a cheque in 4 starts second-up in the past, and from the pole position, he can't be taken lightly. Include in all multiples.
